#Text=President-Elect Obama 's inaugural donations to be listed online

#Text=The Presidential Inaugural Committee says it is " taking unprecedented steps to insure transparency in the public reporting of donors " by listing the names of individuals or organizations who donate over $ 200 towards President-Elect Barack Obama 's upcoming inaugural .

column1: #Text=Logging onto http://www.pic2009.org/page/content/donors/ will show you a current list of over 169 current donors who have given at least that amount , and for most of the donors , much more .
#Text=Donors include movie stars , real estate moguls , and sports stars , many of whom also contributed to Obama 's presidential campaign .

#Text=The Presidential Inaugural Committee states that it has raised almost $ 10 million dollars to cover the inaugural ; and while that may seem like a large amount , the spending record for an inaugural is held by the current president , George W. Bush , with $ 42.8 million spent on his 2004 inaugural .
#Text=Nikita Stewart .
#Text=" Inaugural Donations to Be Listed Online " — The Washington Post , December 13 , 2008
#Text=Emily Cadei .
#Text=" Obama Has Raised $ 10 million " — CQ Politics , December 12 , 2008
#Text=Scientists detect black hole at center of Milky Way Galaxy
#Text=American and German astronomers have detected and confirmed that there is a ' super-massive ' black hole at the center of the Milky Way galaxy .
#Text=It is approximately 27,000 light years from Earth , and four million times bigger than the Sun .
#Text=Scientists say it plays a significant role in forming all galaxies .
#Text=The 16-year study was performed using two telescopes located in Chile .
#Text=They discovered it by tracking the movement of over two dozen separate stars .
#Text=The study will be published next month in The Astrophysical Journal .
#Text=Sources
#Text=Matt Schofield .
#Text=" Massive black hole confirmed at heart of our galaxy " — Kansas City Star , December 10 , 2008
#Text=Pallab Ghosh .
#Text=" Black hole confirmed in Milky Way " — BBC News Online , December 9 , 2008
#Text=Zimbabwe accuses United Kingdom of causing cholera epidemic

#Text=An ally of Zimbabwean president Robert Mugabe , Information Minister Sikhanyiso Ndlovu , has said that a cholera epidemic in the country , which killed hundreds of people , was caused by the United Kingdom .
#Text=Ndlovu said of the outbreak that it was a " genocidal onslaught on the people of Zimbabwe by the British .

#Text=Colombia extradites drug lord to the United States
#Text=File : Dondiegomontoya . png
#Text=Montoya 's mugshot ( Image missing from commons : image ; log )
#Text=Diego Montoya , who is alleged to be one of the Colombia 's most powerful drug lords , has been handed over to the United States authorities by Colombia to face trial .
#Text=Montoya will face 12 charges , including those of murder , money laundering , and the trafficking of drugs .
#Text=If convicted , he will serve no less than twenty years in prison .
#Text=Montoya was the leader of the Norte del Valle cartel , which is reported to have exported 70 % of all the cocaine sold in both the European Union and the United States at its height .
#Text=He was on the U.S. Federal Bureau of Investigation 's " Top Ten " most wanted fugitives .
#Text=Sources
#Text=" Colombia hands ' drug lord ' to US " — BBC News , December 12 , 2008
#Text=" Colombia extradites top drug suspect Diego Montoya to US " — dailypress.com , December 12 , 2008
#Text=Rare snowfall strikes southern United States
#Text=Snow has started falling in some southern states of the US , including Louisiana and Mississippi .

#Text=As much as eight inches of snow were recorded , and thousands of people were left without power - one of Louisiana 's largest power suppliers , Cleco Corporation , reported ten thousand outages .
#Text=Forecasters warned of dangerous driving conditions , and some flights at Louis Armstrong International Airport , located near New Orleans , were affected .
#Text=In New Orleans , snow fell today for the first time in four years .
#Text=The largest snowfall amount for the city ever recorded is about 5 inches , on December 30 , 1963 .
#Text=Sources
#Text=" Southern US hit by rare snowfall " — BBC News , December 12 , 2008
#Text=" Rare snow covers south Louisiana , Miss. " — Netscape News , December 12 , 2008
#Text=Pin-up queen Bettie Page dies at age 85
#Text=Bettie Page , a model who became famous for her pin-up photos , has died at the age of 85 .
#Text=Page died of complications from a heart attack on Thursday , December 11 .
#Text=She was born Bettie Mae Page on April 22 , 1923 in Nashville , Tennessee .
#Text=She was also one of the earliest Playmates of the Month for Playboy magazine .
#Text=Sources
#Text=" 50s pin-up queen Bettie Page dies " — BBC News Online , December 12 , 2008
#Text=AP .
#Text=" 1950s pinup model Bettie Page dies in LA at 85 " — Associated Press , December 12 , 2008
#Text=Estonian law to allow voting by cell phone
#Text=The Parliament of Estonia has passed a law that will allow citizens to vote by mobile phone in the 2011 parliamentary elections .
#Text=Voters will need free , authorized chips for their phones .
#Text=In last year 's elections , Estonians voted online .
#Text=The country 's Reform Party proposed mobile voting in September 2007 .
#Text=Sources
#Text=Jari Tanner .
#Text=" Estonia to vote by mobile phone in 2011 " — Associated Press , December 12 , 2008
#Text=The Baltic Times staff and wire reports .
#Text=" Lithuania ready for e-voting , but Estonia 's already onto m-voting " — The Baltic Times , September 27 , 2007
